  "texts": [
    "However, most current research focuses on hyperspectral data reconstruction in the visible (400-700 nm) and short-wave infrared (400-1000 nm) spectra.",
    "Extending this reconstruction to cover the entire vis-NIR spectrum (400-2500 nm) could greatly enhance applications in food safety, traceability and authenticity verification.",
    "Nevertheless, the complexity of this task increases with the number of spectral bands involved.",
    "Therefore, strategically selecting key spectral features for reconstruction could be a practical approach to managing this complexity (i.e., product and quality attributes specificity).",
    "While hyperspectral image reconstruction techniques show promise in agri-food systems, completely replacing traditional hyperspectral imaging methods is not straightforward."
  ],
